We first identify the numbers we will be using in the calculation. In this problem, the Operating Cash Flow Ratio is defined as follows:

  Operating Cash Flow Ratio = Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities / Total Current Liabilities

From the provided balance sheet (end amounts) and cash flow statement, we have:

 • Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = 803237.11

 • Total Current Liabilities = 1548001.20

Now, we compute:

  803237.11 ÷ 1548001.20 ≈ 0.5189

Rounded to two decimal places, this becomes approximately 0.52.

Thus, the Operating Cash Flow Ratio is approximately 0.52.

The answer in the required JSON format is:

{"solution": {"Operating Cash Flow Ratio": "0.52"}}
